<p>This can, however, be easily fixed by installing <a href="https://www.rforge.net/rJava/files/">rJava from RForge.net</a> as stated <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33550437/install-rjava-one-or-more-jni-types-differ-from-the-corresponding-native-type">here</a>. Running <code>install.packages('&lt;PATH TO DOWNLOAD&gt;/rJava_0.9-8.tar.gz', repos = NULL, type="source")</code> installed the current rJava version properly.</p>

<h2>Loading rJava in RStudio fails</h2>

<p>I&rsquo;ve set up my homebrew R version properly using <code>R CMD javareconf JAVA_CPPFLAGS="-I/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Headers -I/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_31.jdk/"</code> as statet in the caveats of the install. Also, <code>/usr/libexec/java_home</code> yields the proper path.</p>

<p>Loading rJava in R through the shell works fine. Loading RStudio with <code>LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$(/usr/libexec/java_home)/jre/lib/server: open -a RStudio</code> and loading rJava does not. It yields the same error as before:</p>

